Distrurbance is defined as the total or partial loss of biomass from an area by causes other than senescence (Chapman and Johnson 1990). Therefore, harvesting is a type of disturbance that may alter the structure and dynamics of kelp beds. This study aimed were to estimate the potential harvest of E. maxima at Danger Point, and to assess the consequences of harvesting whole sporophytes on kelp recruitment, regrowth, and the understorey community.

