esent. Criteria for the delineation of marine biogeographical regions are criti- cally discussed, and it is concluded that the monitoring of distributions of all species, including rare species, is necessary. This is particularly relevant with regard to using these data to assess effects of potential changes in seawater temperature, including those which may be caused by global warming. Criteria for the delimitation of biogeographic entities such as ‘‘marine provinces'' need to be clearly spelt out in all investigations.},
